{
  "body": "The site is hosted on at least two subdomains, `docs` and `doc`. This practice directly counters the vision expressed in the readme file: \"doc.perl6.org to become the No. 1 resource\" because\n- the value of inbound links is scattered\n- duplicated content is penalised in search engines as this is a tactic employed by Web spammers\n\nThe best solution is to permanently redirect all pages to `doc` which is the one host name mentioned several times in the readme file. For further details: https://duckduckgo.com/?q=seo+canonicalisation\n",
